messageBody:
--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, Paige Gabhart <pgabhart@a...>
wrote:


> > be done rather easily I think -- except for the lack of a
> > monospace
> > font for JQS). Voila! The entire system in QS (almost)!
>
> I don't even know what JQS is!

Sorry. Just made it up.

JQS = Junior Quick Script
SQS = Senior " "

A 'locale' is a tag to indicate a language and a region used in modern
computers. It is used to choose which message catalogs (files which
contain messages for programs like "File Not Found") a program should
use and other culture dependent things like what the number separator
should be (a dot or a comma) or the radix (for decimals - a dot or a
comma) what the default money symbol should be (euro, dollar, pounds
sterling, etc) and what spelling dictionary to use (color versus
colour). The locale for american english is en_US, for british english
en_GB.
